        <refentrytitle>gl_GlobalInvocationID</refentrytitle>
        <manvolnum>3G</manvolnum>
    </refmeta>
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>gl_GlobalInvocationID</refname>
        <refpurpose>contains the global index of work item currently being operated on by a compute shader</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv><title>Declaration</title>
        <funcsynopsis>
            <function>in uvec3 gl_GlobalInvocationID</function>
        </funcsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsect1 id="description"><title>Description</title>
        <para>
            In the compute language, <function>gl_GlobalInvocationID</function>
            is a derived input variable containing the n-dimensional index of the
            work invocation within the global work group that the current shader is
            executing on. The value of <function>gl_GlobalInvocationID</function> is equal to
            <function>gl_WorkGroupID</function> * <function>gl_WorkGroupSize</function> + <function>gl_LocalInvocationID</function>.
        </para>
    </refsect1>
